body_text:
Currently, document sidebar ordering is determined by front matter that has to be manually written in each of the docs. User feedback indicated that it may be tedious to have to manage this front matter, especially when there are large numbers of docs.
This new script uses a .json file with the sidebar information to write front matter headers into doc files so that users do not have to manually manage front matter for ordering by changing the previous and next fields. This does not change any of how Docusaurus reads front matter and uses that information, and users may still provide all of the information manually without running this script or having the .json file.
An example .json file, which separates sidebars, and uses document categories and ids:
{
  "docs": {
    "Docusaurus": ["doc1"],
    "First Category": ["doc2"],
    "Second Category": ["doc3"]
  },
  "docs-other": {
    "First Category": ["doc4", "doc5"]
  }
}
Users no longer have to manually enter the layout, category, next, or previous fields in the front matter.
Docs will be written to describe this functionality, and the fact that it is optional and any current manually-written front matter will still work.
Current plans also include changing the layout field to be called sidebar (while allowing both so current sites don't break), but that will be part of a different pr.

